{title: Are Ye Able Said The Master}
{artist: Burl Ives}
{composer: Written by Earl Bowman Marlatt and Harry Silverdale Mason}

[G]Are ye able said the [C]Master
To be cruci[D7]fied with [G]Me
Yea the sturdy dreamers answered[C]
To the [A7]death we follow [D7]Thee
[G]Lord [B7]we are [Em]able our [C]spirits are [G]Thine
[D7]Remold them [G]make us [D7]like [A7]Thee [D7]divine
[G]Thy [B7]guiding [Em]radiance [C]above us shall [B7]be
A [C]beacon to [G]God to [B7]love and [D7]loyal[G]ty
Are ye able to [C]remember
When a [D7]thief lifts up his [G]eyes
That his pardoned soul is [C]worthy
Of a [A7]place in para[D7]dise
[G]Lord [B7]we are [Em]able our [C]spirits are [G]Thine
[D7]Remold them [G]make us [D7]like [A7]Thee [D7]divine
[G]Thy [B7]guiding [Em]radiance [C]above us shall [B7]be
A [C]beacon to [G]God to [B7]love and [D7]loyal[G]ty
Are ye able while the [C]Master
Whispers [D7]down eterni[G]ty
And heroic spirits [C]answer
Now as [A7]then in Gali[D7]lee
